    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Tags include `bff-api`; modifies 4 BFF services in `Services/Ai/` boundary; NFR-07 pre-fill flow invariants are binding (signatures, 45s timeout, `useAiPrefill` + `$choices` contract); FULL per task-execute Step 0.5.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>1-M</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Migrate 4 Pattern A BFF consumers from `WorkspaceOptions.*PlaybookId` env-var reads to `IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync` calls per spec FR-1R-05. The 4 consumers are `MatterPreFillService`, `ProjectPreFillService`, `WorkspaceAiService`, and `WorkspaceFileEndpoints`. NFR-07 is binding for the two pre-fill services: signatures unchanged, 45s timeout preserved, `useAiPrefill` + `$choices` contract unchanged. `WorkspaceAiService` must preserve graceful-degrade fallback. `WorkspaceFileEndpoints` must preserve FR-04 fail-fast on missing playbook AND now passes `mimeType` via `RoutingContext` so the `sprk_matchconditions` JSON predicate can route by content type. Each service receives `IConsumerRoutingService` via constructor injection (Scoped lifetime). One integration test per service confirms identical behavior post-migration vs the Phase 1 baseline. Final grep proves zero remaining `WorkspaceOptions.*PlaybookId` reads in `Services/` (the deprecation telemetry call site wired by 028e is the only exception).
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in chat-routing layer + Phase 1 stable-code migration history + NFR-07 pre-fill flow invariants.</role>

  <goal>
    All 4 Pattern A consumers (`MatterPreFillService`, `ProjectPreFillService`, `WorkspaceAiService`, `WorkspaceFileEndpoints`) resolve their playbook target via `IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync(consumerType, [consumerCode], [context])` from the `sprk_playbookconsumer` Dataverse table seeded by 028b. NFR-07 signatures + 45s pre-fill timeout + `useAiPrefill` / `$choices` contract preserved verbatim for the two pre-fill services. 4 integration tests (one per service) pass against the migrated codepath and confirm identical behavior to the Phase 1 baseline. Final `Grep` over `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/` for `WorkspaceOptions.MatterPreFillPlaybookId`, `WorkspaceOptions.ProjectPreFillPlaybookId`, `WorkspaceOptions.AiSummaryPlaybookId`, `WorkspaceOptions.SummarizePlaybookId` returns zero hits (one expected hit per name lands in 028e's deprecation telemetry site).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec §"Phase 1R" FR-1R-05 + the 2026-06-24 UAT-2 failure that motivated this phase. Phase 1 migrated callers to resolve playbooks by stable CODE (chat-summarize, matter-pre-fill, etc.) — but the binding `code → playbookid GUID` was still configured via `Workspace__*PlaybookId` environment variables. Phase 1R replaces that env-var binding with the `sprk_playbookconsumer` Dataverse table (FR-1R-01) queried through the `IConsumerRoutingService` (built in task 028a) and seeded by `Seed-PlaybookConsumers.ps1` (task 028b). This task migrates the 4 "Pattern A" consumers (those that previously read typed-options `WorkspaceOptions.*PlaybookId` directly). Two of them (`MatterPreFillService`, `ProjectPreFillService`) are NFR-07 critical paths — pre-fill UX must remain identical (signature, 45s timeout, `useAiPrefill` flag, `$choices` shape) per Phase 1 task 018 evidence. `WorkspaceAiService` ships AI summary tiles with graceful-degrade fallback if no playbook configured (UI tile still renders) — that behavior must be preserved. `WorkspaceFileEndpoints` (FR-04 fail-fast) is the canonical consumer that uses the `RoutingContext.MimeType` match key from FR-1R-04, demonstrating context-aware routing for the `sprk_matchconditions` JSON predicate.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Routing/IConsumerRoutingService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Routing/ConsumerRoutingService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Workspace/MatterPreFillService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Workspace/ProjectPreFillService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Workspace/WorkspaceAiService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Endpoints/WorkspaceFileEndpoints.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Configuration/WorkspaceOptions.cs</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Workspace/MatterPreFillServiceTests.cs</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Workspace/ProjectPreFillServiceTests.cs</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Workspace/WorkspaceAiServiceTests.cs</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Endpoints/WorkspaceFileEndpointsTests.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-1R-05">All 4 Pattern A consumers migrate to `IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync`; final grep returns zero `WorkspaceOptions.*PlaybookId` reads in `Services/` except the deprecation telemetry call site (wired by 028e).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Stays in `Services/Ai/` boundary; no CRUD-code violations.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task BFF publish-size measurement; report delta vs current baseline (~45.65 MB).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">`IConsumerRoutingService` injected via ctor; no `IServiceProvider.GetService&lt;T&gt;()` in endpoint signatures.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">`ResolveAsync` honors 5-min TTL per-tenant cache from task 028a — consumers MUST NOT add a second cache layer.</constraint>
    <constraint source="hardening (code-review S-5)">Use the `ConsumerTypes` constants from `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PublicContracts/ConsumerTypes.cs` — NEVER pass literal strings. `MatterPreFillService` calls `ResolveAsync(ConsumerTypes.MatterPreFill)`; `ProjectPreFillService` uses `ConsumerTypes.ProjectPreFill`; `WorkspaceAiService` uses `ConsumerTypes.AiSummary`; `WorkspaceFileEndpoints` uses `ConsumerTypes.SummarizeFile`. Compile-time typo defense per the 2026-06-24 code-review S-5 recommendation.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">NFR-07 pre-fill flow contracts preserved — signatures, 45s timeout, `useAiPrefill` / `$choices` unchanged.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">`WorkspaceAiService` graceful-degrade fallback preserved — UI tile still renders when no playbook is configured (per Phase 1 task 018 evidence).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">`WorkspaceFileEndpoints` fail-fast (FR-04) preserved AND now passes `RoutingContext.MimeType = file.ContentType` so `sprk_matchconditions` can route by MIME.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Test update obligation (CLAUDE.md §10) — add/update one integration test per migrated consumer; existing Phase 1 tests remain unchanged or are extended in place.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
