  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `IConsumerRoutingService.cs` from task 028a output to confirm the final method signature, `RoutingContext` shape, and DI registration lifetime (Scoped). Read `WorkspaceOptions.cs` to confirm the four `*PlaybookId` properties slated for deprecation.</step>
    <step order="2">Read `MatterPreFillService.cs` end-to-end; identify every read of `WorkspaceOptions.MatterPreFillPlaybookId`. Note the NFR-07 contract surface (method signatures, 45s timeout, `useAiPrefill` + `$choices` flow).</step>
    <step order="3">Migrate `MatterPreFillService`: inject `IConsumerRoutingService` via ctor; replace `_workspaceOptions.MatterPreFillPlaybookId` with `await _consumerRouting.ResolveAsync("matter-pre-fill", ct: ct)`; preserve every NFR-07 invariant verbatim. Update existing tests + add one integration test asserting identical behavior pre/post migration (use Phase 1 task 018 test as baseline).</step>
    <step order="4">Migrate `ProjectPreFillService`: same pattern as Step 3 — inject `IConsumerRoutingService`; replace `_workspaceOptions.ProjectPreFillPlaybookId` with `await _consumerRouting.ResolveAsync("project-pre-fill", ct: ct)`; preserve NFR-07. Add integration test.</step>
    <step order="5">Migrate `WorkspaceAiService`: inject `IConsumerRoutingService`; replace `_workspaceOptions.AiSummaryPlaybookId` with `await _consumerRouting.ResolveAsync("ai-summary", ct: ct)`; preserve graceful-degrade fallback — if `ResolveAsync` returns `null`, the AI summary tile must still render with the existing "no summary configured" placeholder. Add integration test asserting null-return path.</step>
    <step order="6">Migrate `WorkspaceFileEndpoints`: inject `IConsumerRoutingService` (via minimal-API parameter or service-locator-by-ctor pattern per ADR-010); replace `_workspaceOptions.SummarizePlaybookId` with `await consumerRouting.ResolveAsync("summarize-file", consumerCode: "default", context: new RoutingContext { MimeType = file.ContentType }, ct: ct)`; preserve FR-04 fail-fast (404 ProblemDetails) when `ResolveAsync` returns `null`. Add integration test with two MIME types to exercise the `mimeType` match-condition.</step>
    <step order="7">Wire DI: confirm each service registration in `Services/Workspace/WorkspaceModule.cs` (or equivalent module file) takes the `IConsumerRoutingService` dependency cleanly; ensure no asymmetric-registration anti-pattern per CLAUDE.md §10 / `bff-extensions.md` §F.1.</step>
    <step order="8">Run the targeted test suites: `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~Workspace"`. Confirm all 4 new integration tests pass + existing tests pass (cumulative test count &gt; 20 expected across the 4 services).</step>
    <step order="9">`Grep` over `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/` for `WorkspaceOptions.MatterPreFillPlaybookId`, `WorkspaceOptions.ProjectPreFillPlaybookId`, `WorkspaceOptions.AiSummaryPlaybookId`, `WorkspaceOptions.SummarizePlaybookId`. Expect zero hits (the deprecation telemetry call site in 028e is allowed but does not exist yet at this task's completion).</step>
    <step order="10">Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` then `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`. Measure compressed publish size; record absolute size + delta vs current baseline (~45.65 MB) per ADR-029 / CLAUDE.md §10. Expect minor delta only (consumers swap one read for one call).</step>
    <step order="11">9.5 quality gates — invoke `code-review` skill + `adr-check` skill. Resolve any findings before marking task complete.</step>
    <step order="12">Write `notes/handoffs/028c-pattern-a-migration-evidence.md` with: per-service diff summary, integration test pass/fail counts, grep evidence (zero hits), publish-size delta, and the NFR-07 invariant verification checklist for the two pre-fill services.</step>
    <step order="13">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 028c → ✅; current-task.md → ready for 028e (after 028d also lands).</step>
  </steps>

