  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`MatterPreFillService` resolves playbook via `_consumerRouting.ResolveAsync("matter-pre-fill")`; NFR-07 invariants preserved (signature, 45s timeout, `useAiPrefill`, `$choices`).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`ProjectPreFillService` resolves playbook via `_consumerRouting.ResolveAsync("project-pre-fill")`; NFR-07 invariants preserved.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`WorkspaceAiService` resolves playbook via `_consumerRouting.ResolveAsync("ai-summary")`; graceful-degrade fallback preserved (UI tile renders even when null returned).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`WorkspaceFileEndpoints` resolves playbook via `_consumerRouting.ResolveAsync("summarize-file", consumerCode: "default", context: { MimeType })`; FR-04 fail-fast preserved.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">4 integration tests (one per service) pass; cumulative Workspace test count &gt; 20.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Grep over `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/` for `WorkspaceOptions.MatterPreFillPlaybookId|ProjectPreFillPlaybookId|AiSummaryPlaybookId|SummarizePlaybookId` returns zero hits.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF publish-size delta reported; cumulative within NFR-01 ceiling (≤60 MB).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`code-review` + `adr-check` exit 0.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Parallel-safe with 028d — separate consumer files. The two pre-fill services are NFR-07 critical paths; do NOT change their method signatures even slightly. The `WorkspaceAiService` graceful-degrade is the canonical example of "soft-fail" routing — a null return from `ResolveAsync` must NOT propagate as an exception. The `WorkspaceFileEndpoints` integration test is also the first end-to-end validation of FR-1R-04 `sprk_matchconditions` MIME routing; consider seeding 2 test routing records (PDF + DOCX) for this test in the test fixture.
  </notes>

